title: fanoutqa: What are the 5 countries with the highest reported cases of COVID-19 and when did the outbreak begin in each of these countries? (1244f9eb0096a5f2)

chat_history.content: What are the 5 countries with the highest reported cases of COVID-19 and when did the outbreak begin in each of these countries?

As of my last update (January 2023), the top five countries with the highest COVID-19 cases are:

1. United States: Over 98 million cases reported. The first confirmed case of COVID-19 in the US was identified on January 20, 2020.
2. India: Over 44.6 million cases. India reported its first case on January 30, 2020.
3. France: Approximately 36.7 million cases. France's first confirmed case was reported on January 24, 2020.
4. Brazil: More than 35.8 million cases. The outbreak in Brazil started with the first case reported on February 26, 2020.
5. Germany: Over 35.4 million cases. Germany's first case was documented on January 27, 2020.

It's essential to note that these numbers might have changed since my cut-off date, and the ongoing nature of the pandemic means that case counts are continually evolving.
